indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who seek information about COVID-19 on a weekly basis
title: COVID-19 World Survey Data API

question: Aware of government disseminating knowledge due to COVID-19
indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who have access to appropriate information on COVID-19
title: Harmonized COVID-19 Household Monitoring Surveys
details: The dataset contains harmonized indicators created from high-frequency phone surveys collected by the World Bank and partners. The surveys capture the socioeconomic impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic on households and individuals from all developing regions. Data are available for over 90 indicators in 14 topic areas, including education, food security, income, safety nets, and others. For more information, please refer to our Technical Note and Data Dictionary.
authors: World Bank
source_comment: The figures presented in this dashboard are derived from the Rapid Monitoring Database (RMD). The RMD is a harmonized collection of high-frequency phone surveys in response to the COVID-19 crisis conducted by the World Bank Group and partners so that they share a common format. In cases where countries had recently conducted representative household survey that contains re-contact information for some or all household members, this data was often used to create a representative sampling frame for telephone-based surveys. In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

question: Last week, did you wash your hands with soap more often than you used to? - Y
indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who report practicing recommended measures to protect themselves from COVID-19
title: Harmonized COVID-19 Household Monitoring Surveys
details: The dataset contains harmonized indicators created from high-frequency phone surveys collected by the World Bank and partners. The surveys capture the socioeconomic impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic on households and individuals from all developing regions. Data are available for over 90 indicators in 14 topic areas, including education, food security, income, safety nets, and others. For more information, please refer to our Technical Note and Data Dictionary.
authors: World Bank
source_comment: The figures presented in this dashboard are derived from the Rapid Monitoring Database (RMD). The RMD is a harmonized collection of high-frequency phone surveys in response to the COVID-19 crisis conducted by the World Bank Group and partners so that they share a common format. In cases where countries had recently conducted representative household survey that contains re-contact information for some or all household members, this data was often used to create a representative sampling frame for telephone-based surveys. In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who report practicing recommended measures to protect themselves from COVID-19
title: Harmonized COVID-19 Household Monitoring Surveys
details: The dataset contains harmonized indicators created from high-frequency phone surveys collected by the World Bank and partners. The surveys capture the socioeconomic impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic on households and individuals from all developing regions. Data are available for over 90 indicators in 14 topic areas, including education, food security, income, safety nets, and others. For more information, please refer to our Technical Note and Data Dictionary.
authors: World Bank
source_comment: The figures presented in this dashboard are derived from the Rapid Monitoring Database (RMD). The RMD is a harmonized collection of high-frequency phone surveys in response to the COVID-19 crisis conducted by the World Bank Group and partners so that they share a common format. In cases where countries had recently conducted representative household survey that contains re-contact information for some or all household members, this data was often used to create a representative sampling frame for telephone-based surveys. In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

question: Adopted social distancing / Avoided gatherings of more than 10 people
indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who report practicing recommended measures to protect themselves from COVID-19
title: Harmonized COVID-19 Household Monitoring Surveys
details: The dataset contains harmonized indicators created from high-frequency phone surveys collected by the World Bank and partners. The surveys capture the socioeconomic impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic on households and individuals from all developing regions. Data are available for over 90 indicators in 14 topic areas, including education, food security, income, safety nets, and others. For more information, please refer to our Technical Note and Data Dictionary.
authors: World Bank
source_comment: The figures presented in this dashboard are derived from the Rapid Monitoring Database (RMD). The RMD is a harmonized collection of high-frequency phone surveys in response to the COVID-19 crisis conducted by the World Bank Group and partners so that they share a common format. In cases where countries had recently conducted representative household survey that contains re-contact information for some or all household members, this data was often used to create a representative sampling frame for telephone-based surveys. In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

question: If a vaccine to prevent coronavirus was available right now at no cost, would you agree to be vaccinated? - Yes
indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who would get vaccinated once a vaccine is available and recommended
title: Gallup World Poll - Over 1 Billion Worldwide Unwilling to Take COVID-19 Vaccine
details: In the first full year of the COVID-19 pandemic, the majority of adults worldwide (68%) told Gallup that they would agree to be vaccinated if a coronavirus vaccine were available to them at no cost. However, like the global number, in most countries, the percentages fell short of the estimated 70% to 90% that some experts say would need to be vaccinated to achieve herd immunity in a population.
authors: Gallup World Poll - Julie Ray
source_comment: These results are based on mobile and landline telephone interviews with approximately 1,000 adults in each country and area, aged 15 and older, conducted in 2020 in 116 countries and areas. For results based on the total sample of national adults, the margin of sampling error ranges between 2.2 and 5.5 percentage points at the 95% confidence level. The margin of error reflects the influence of data weighting. In addition to sampling error, question wording and practical difficulties in conducting surveys can introduce error or bias into the findings of public opinion polls.

question: Plan to take COVID-19 vaccine
indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who would get vaccinated once a vaccine is available and recommended
title: Harmonized COVID-19 Household Monitoring Surveys
details: The dataset contains harmonized indicators created from high-frequency phone surveys collected by the World Bank and partners. The surveys capture the socioeconomic impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic on households and individuals from all developing regions. Data are available for over 90 indicators in 14 topic areas, including education, food security, income, safety nets, and others. For more information, please refer to our Technical Note and Data Dictionary.
authors: World Bank
source_comment: The figures presented in this dashboard are derived from the Rapid Monitoring Database (RMD). The RMD is a harmonized collection of high-frequency phone surveys in response to the COVID-19 crisis conducted by the World Bank Group and partners so that they share a common format. In cases where countries had recently conducted representative household survey that contains re-contact information for some or all household members, this data was often used to create a representative sampling frame for telephone-based surveys. In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who report COVID-19 has had a negative economic impact on their life
title: Harmonized COVID-19 Household Monitoring Surveys
details: The dataset contains harmonized indicators created from high-frequency phone surveys collected by the World Bank and partners. The surveys capture the socioeconomic impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic on households and individuals from all developing regions. Data are available for over 90 indicators in 14 topic areas, including education, food security, income, safety nets, and others. For more information, please refer to our Technical Note and Data Dictionary.
authors: World Bank
source_comment: The figures presented in this dashboard are derived from the Rapid Monitoring Database (RMD). The RMD is a harmonized collection of high-frequency phone surveys in response to the COVID-19 crisis conducted by the World Bank Group and partners so that they share a common format. In cases where countries had recently conducted representative household survey that contains re-contact information for some or all household members, this data was often used to create a representative sampling frame for telephone-based surveys. In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

question: Total income decreased / Stopped working since COVID-19 outbreak
indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who report COVID-19 has had a negative economic impact on their life
title: Harmonized COVID-19 Household Monitoring Surveys
details: The dataset contains harmonized indicators created from high-frequency phone surveys collected by the World Bank and partners. The surveys capture the socioeconomic impacts of the COVID-19 pandemic on households and individuals from all developing regions. Data are available for over 90 indicators in 14 topic areas, including education, food security, income, safety nets, and others. For more information, please refer to our Technical Note and Data Dictionary.
authors: World Bank
source_comment: The figures presented in this dashboard are derived from the Rapid Monitoring Database (RMD). The RMD is a harmonized collection of high-frequency phone surveys in response to the COVID-19 crisis conducted by the World Bank Group and partners so that they share a common format. In cases where countries had recently conducted representative household survey that contains re-contact information for some or all household members, this data was often used to create a representative sampling frame for telephone-based surveys. In other cases, list-based sampling frames used numbers from government registries, telecommunications companies, marketing firms, or other sources to survey representative samples. See more on: https://datacatalog.worldbank.org/dataset/harmonized-covid-19-household-monitoring-surveys

question: Have you been tested for COVID-19 in the past 14 days? - Yes
limitation: Facebook users only, Limited sample size
indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who have been tested for COVID-19
title: COVID-19 World Survey Data API
details: This is an API for accessing the daily COVID-19 World Symptoms Survey data. Data calculated based on the Facebook global symptoms survey data. Using the survey data, we estimate the percentage of people in a given country or region.

indicator_name: Percentage of individuals who experienced difficulties in getting vaccinated
title: COVID-19 World Survey Data API
